<!-- Philosophy band -->
<section class="section section--sunk fade-up">
  <div class="container narrow center-text">
    <p class="t-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">The relational philosophy</p>
    <h2 class="t-h2 t-balance" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);">A living relational ecology, not three services</h2>
    <p class="t-lead t-pretty">One-to-one is individual depth. Circles are small-group relational reflection. Live explorations are collective perspective. Together they form one body — different sizes of the same conversation about what it means to be human, in this age, with each other.</p>
    <p class="t-meta" style="margin-top: var(--sp-6); font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-size: var(--fs-md);">
      You are allowed to arrive as you are.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- What these are NOT — softly named -->
<section class="section fade-up">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <div class="section-header" style="text-align: left; align-items: flex-start; margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);">
      <p class="t-eyebrow">A note on tone</p>
      <h2 class="t-h2 t-balance">What these spaces are not</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="t-body" style="color: var(--c-ink-soft); font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-lg); line-height: 1.5;">
      Not coaching. Not therapy. Not group programmes. Not webinars or motivational speaking. No countdowns. No scarcity language. No funnels that get faster the longer you stay. No experts and seekers — only humans, with each other, looking carefully at what is here.
    </p>
    <p class="t-body" style="margin-top: var(--sp-5);">If a space asks for money, it asks once, in plain words, with care — because the work has to be sustainable to remain itself.</p>
  </div>
</section>

